@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@
+---
+date: "2026-06-11"
+status: done
+implements: [FR-E83]
+tags: [engine, recovery, cli, journal]
+related_tasks:
+  - 2026/05/durable-run-lifecycle-replay.md
+---
+# engine: `runs doctor` journal health checker
+
+## Goal
+
+Add `flowai-workflow runs doctor` so operators can diagnose one run's durable
+recovery artifacts, report every detected problem, and apply only safe
+mechanical repairs for crash-torn journal tails and stale run locks.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 made `<workflow>/runs/<run-id>/journal.jsonl` the durable recovery
+contract. The replayer tolerates duplicate event IDs and a malformed partial
+tail, but operators do not yet have a CLI health checker that separates safe
+crash artifacts from semantic corruption.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns `getJournalPath()` and
+  `replayRunJournal()`.
+- `src/state/state.ts` owns `getRunDir()` and node path helpers.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` owns `defaultLockPath()` and lock parsing.
+- `src/cli.ts` has direct subcommand dispatch for `run`, `answer`, `init`,
+  and `mcp`; there is no `runs` command group.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Reuse `replayRunJournal()` as the single replay source of truth.
+- Reuse existing state and lock helpers for paths and lock parsing.
+- Add no dependencies.
+- Report all findings before choosing the exit code.
+- `--repair` may only remove a torn final journal line and a stale lock for
+  this run; semantic corruption is a refusal.
+- The benchmark is non-interactive. Variant gate decision: selected
+  "dedicated doctor module plus CLI dispatcher" because it keeps CLI parsing
+  local while isolating diagnosis and repair logic for direct unit tests.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] FR-E83: `runs doctor` clean-run diagnosis exits 0 and reports OK.
+      Test: `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 clean run exits ok`.
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: journal integrity diagnostics cover torn final line warning,
+      mid-file garbage error, unknown event kind error, non-monotonic sequence,
+      and duplicate event ID warning. Tests:
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 torn final line is warning`,
+      `FR-E83 mid-file garbage is error`, `FR-E83 unknown event kind is error`,
+      `FR-E83 sequence and duplicate ids are reported`. Evidence command:
+      `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: replay invariant diagnostics cover events after terminal run
+      events, undeclared node lifecycle events, attempt completion without a
+      matching start, and total-cost divergence. Tests:
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 replay invariants report semantic problems`.
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: filesystem cross-check diagnostics cover orphan node dirs,
+      missing declared dirs, and stale locks. Tests:
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 filesystem cross-check reports orphan missing and stale lock`.
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `--repair` removes only a torn final journal line with
+      `journal.jsonl.bak` preserved and removes stale lock; it refuses live
+      locks and semantic journal errors without modifying files. Tests:
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 repair torn tail preserves backup and replays cleanly`,
+      `FR-E83 repair refuses live lock`, `FR-E83 repair refuses mid-file garbage`.
+      Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `--json` emits machine-readable findings with severity, code,
+      message, and evidence path; CLI help mentions `runs doctor`. Tests:
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 json output shape`,
+      `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 help mentions runs doctor`. Evidence command:
+      `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: SRS registers `runs doctor` in
+      `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`,
+      `documents/requirements-engine.md`, and `documents/index.md`, with
+      acceptance references filled. Evidence command: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: full project verification passes. Test:
+      `scripts/check.ts::full check pipeline`. Evidence command:
+      `deno task check`.
+
+## Solution
+
+1. Add `src/state/run-doctor.ts`.
+   - Define `DoctorFinding` and `DoctorReport` with severities `ERROR`,
+     `WARNING`, and `OK`.
+   - Parse `journal.jsonl` line-by-line for integrity findings and record line
+     numbers, valid byte length, torn-tail status, declared nodes, declared
+     node directories, mentioned nodes, event IDs, and sequence order.
+   - Validate known `RunJournalEventKind` values locally from a static set that
+     mirrors the public union, while replay state still comes exclusively from
+     `replayRunJournal()`.
+   - Invoke `replayRunJournal(runDir)` once for replay-derived state and
+     duplicate-tail behavior; catch replay errors as findings rather than
+     aborting the scan.
+   - Inspect replay invariants from parsed events: post-terminal events,
+     undeclared lifecycle nodes, unmatched attempt completions, and total cost
+     mismatch between replayed total and per-node sum.
+   - Cross-check the run directory: direct child node dirs plus phase child
+     node dirs are compared with `node_directory_declared` event paths; `logs`,
+     `worktree`, and dot-prefixed engine metadata are ignored. Use
+     `defaultLockPath()` and `readLockInfo()` for lock checks.
+   - Implement `repairRun()` guardrails: refuse active live lock, refuse any
+     journal error besides a torn final line, then back up and atomically
+     rewrite the journal without the torn tail and remove stale lock.
+
+2. Add tests in `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts`.
+   - Fabricate isolated workflow and run dirs with minimal journal events.
+   - Cover every requested diagnostic and repair case.
+   - Assert repair round-trip with `replayRunJournal()` after the rewrite.
+
+3. Wire the CLI in `src/cli.ts`.
+   - Parse `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+     [--repair] [--json]`.
+   - Render grouped human output by severity or JSON findings.
+   - Exit 0 when no `ERROR` findings remain, exit 1 otherwise, and mention the
+     subcommand in global help.
+
+4. Update documentation.
+   - Add FR-E83 to `documents/requirements-engine.md`.
+   - Add FR-E83 to `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md` with
+     `**Acceptance criteria:**` pointing at the new tests and `deno task check`.
+   - Keep `documents/index.md` row in sync.
+   - Update SDS only where the CLI and recovery subsystem description would be
+     stale after the new command.
+
+5. Verify.
+   - RED: add failing focused tests first.
+   - GREEN/REFACTOR: implement until focused tests pass.
+   - CHECK: run `deno task check`.
+
+## Critique
+
+1. Direct child directory scanning could misclassify phased node dirs if it
+   only checks one level.
+2. A static known-kind set can drift from `RunJournalEventKind` if future
+   journal events are added.
+3. Repair ordering could remove a stale lock before discovering a semantic
+   journal error.
+
+## Refinements
+
+- Applied: scan both flat and one-level phased node directories, while ignoring
+  known runtime metadata directories.
+- Applied: add a code comment near the known-kind set instructing updates when
+  the journal union changes; avoid exporting type-runtime metadata only for
+  doctor.
+- Applied: compute the full report before any repair and refuse repairs when
+  semantic journal errors exist.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- Multi-run batch diagnosis is explicitly out of scope.
